### FHIR R4 API Test Requests
### Use with VS Code REST Client extension

@baseUrl = http://localhost:3000

### Health Check
GET {{baseUrl}}/health

### FHIR Capability Statement
GET {{baseUrl}}/fhir/r4/metadata

### List all Patients
GET {{baseUrl}}/fhir/r4/Patient

### List Patients with pagination
GET {{baseUrl}}/fhir/r4/Patient?_count=5&_offset=0

### List Encounters
GET {{baseUrl}}/fhir/r4/Encounter

### List Observations
GET {{baseUrl}}/fhir/r4/Observation?_count=10

### List Conditions
GET {{baseUrl}}/fhir/r4/Condition

### List Medications
GET {{baseUrl}}/fhir/r4/MedicationRequest

### List Allergies
GET {{baseUrl}}/fhir/r4/AllergyIntolerance

### List Immunizations
GET {{baseUrl}}/fhir/r4/Immunization

### List Procedures
GET {{baseUrl}}/fhir/r4/Procedure

### List Appointments
GET {{baseUrl}}/fhir/r4/Appointment

### List Claims
GET {{baseUrl}}/fhir/r4/Claim

### List Organizations
GET {{baseUrl}}/fhir/r4/Organization

### List Practitioners
GET {{baseUrl}}/fhir/r4/Practitioner

### List Locations
GET {{baseUrl}}/fhir/r4/Location

### Create a Patient
POST {{baseUrl}}/fhir/r4/Patient
Content-Type: application/fhir+json

{
  "resourceType": "Patient",
  "name": [
    {
      "use": "official",
      "family": "TestPatient",
      "given": ["Demo"]
    }
  ],
  "gender": "male",
  "birthDate": "1990-01-15",
  "active": true
}

### OpenAPI Spec
GET {{baseUrl}}/openapi.json
